{"word":"κραδαίνω","slug":"κραδαίνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κραδαίνω</b></el> <el>(κρᾰδαίνω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κραδάω'><el>κραδάω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to swing, wave, brandish</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>: <i>to shake, agitate</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>αἰχμὴ κραδαινομένη κατὰ γαίης</el> <i>quivering</i> in the ground, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to agitate</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}